'''焦慮'''是一種[[情緒|情緒]]，其特徵是內心動蕩的不愉快狀態，包括對預期事件的[[恐懼|恐懼]]的[[主觀|主觀]]不愉快感覺。<ref>{{cite book|title=Abnormal Psychology|url=https://archive.org/details/abnormalpsycholo0000unse_j6d5|vauthors=Davison GC|publisher=Veronica Visentin|year=2008|isbn=978-0-470-84072-6|location=Toronto|page=[https://archive.org/details/abnormalpsycholo0000unse_j6d5/page/154 154]|name-list-style=vanc}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last1=Miceli|first1=Maria|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=z0aPBQAAQBAJ&dq=anticipation+emotion&pg=PP1|title=Expectancy and emotion|last2=Castelfranchi|first2=Cristiano|date=2014-11-27|publisher=OUP Oxford|isbn=978-0-19-150927-8|language=en|access-date=2021-12-16|archive-date=2022-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220106050644/https://books.google.com/books?id=z0aPBQAAQBAJ&dq=anticipation+emotion&pg=PP1|dead-url=no}}</ref>

它通常伴隨著某些行為，例如來回踱步、軀體不適和沈思等。<ref name="Seligman">{{cite book|vauthors=Seligman ME, Walker EF, Rosenhan DL|author3-link=David Rosenhan|author1-link=Martin Seligman|title=Abnormal psychology|year=1989|url=https://archive.org/details/abnormalpsycholo0000rose_k3y9|edition=4th|location=New York|publisher=W.W. Norton & Company}}{{Page needed|date=May 2013}}</ref>

焦慮是一種不安和[[擔心|擔憂]]的[[感覺|感覺]]，通常影響身心各層面，且對主觀上被視為威脅的情況反應過度。<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=E_9Rlqs4T7oC|title=Psychiatric and Behavioral Disorders in Intellectual and Developmental Disabilities|vauthors=Bouras N, Holt G|publisher=Cambridge University Press|year=2007|isbn=9781139461306|edition=2nd|access-date=2021-12-16|archive-date=2020-07-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200726073009/https://books.google.com/books?id=E_9Rlqs4T7oC|dead-url=no}}{{Page needed|date=May 2013}}</ref> 它常伴有肌肉緊張<ref name="DSM-5 189">{{Cite book|last=American Psychiatric Association|year=2013|title=Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders|edition=Fifth|publisher=American Psychiatric Publishing|location=Arlington, VA|page=[https://archive.org/details/diagnosticstatis0005unse/page/189 189]|isbn=978-0-89042-555-8|url=https://archive.org/details/diagnosticstatis0005unse/page/189}}</ref>、煩躁、[[疲勞|疲勞]]、呼吸緊迫、腹部緊繃和注意力不集中等。焦慮與恐懼密切相關，恐懼是對真實或感知到的直接威脅的反應；焦慮涉及對未來威脅的預期，包括恐懼。<ref name="DSM-5 189">{{Cite book|last=American Psychiatric Association|year=2013|title=Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders|edition=Fifth|publisher=American Psychiatric Publishing|location=Arlington, VA|page=[https://archive.org/details/diagnosticstatis0005unse/page/189 189]|isbn=978-0-89042-555-8|url=https://archive.org/details/diagnosticstatis0005unse/page/189}}</ref> 面臨焦慮的人可能會從過去引起焦慮的情況中退縮。<ref name="Barker, P. 2003">{{cite book|vauthors=Barker P|year=2003|title=Psychiatric and Mental Health Nursing: The Craft of Caring|url=https://archive.org/details/psychiatricmenta0000unse_y6b5|publisher=Edward Arnold|location=London|isbn=978-0-340-81026-2}}{{Page needed|date=May 2013}}</ref> 觸發焦慮的原因，可能包括[[身體完整性|身體完整性]]、[[自尊|自尊]]或[[自我形象|自我形象]]等受威脅的預期或經歷等。

焦慮是一種正常的人類反應，但當程度高於常態或持續時間多於常態時，或無法被以合理的方式證明時，可能會被診斷為[[焦慮症|焦慮症]]。有多種形式的焦慮症 (如[[廣泛性焦慮症|廣泛性焦慮症]]和[[強迫症|強迫症]]) 具有特定的[[臨床醫學|臨床]]定義。<ref name="Treating and Preventing Adolescent Mental Health Disorders: What We Know and What We Don't Know. A Research Agenda for Improving the Mental Health of Our Youth">{{cite book|url=https://oxfordmedicine.com/view/10.1093/9780195173642.001.0001/med-9780195173642-chapter-10|publisher=Oxford University Press|publication-place=New York|doi=10.1093/9780195173642.001.0001|title=Treating and preventing adolescent mental health disorders: what we know and what we don't know. A research agenda for improving the mental health of our youth|year=2005|isbn=978-0-19-517364-2|veditors=Evans DL, Foa EB, Gur RE, Hendin H, O'Brien CP, Seligman ME, Walsh BT|oclc=56324679|access-date=2021-12-16|archive-date=2021-12-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211216111841/https://oxfordmedicine.com/view/10.1093/9780195173642.001.0001/med-9780195173642-chapter-10|dead-url=no}}</ref> 將焦慮症與日常焦慮區分開來的部分定義是它是持續性的，通常持續 6 個月或更長時間，儘管持續時間的標準旨在作為一般指南，並允許一定程度的靈活性，並且有時在兒童中持續時間較短。<ref name="DSM-5 189">{{Cite book|last=American Psychiatric Association|year=2013|title=Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders|edition=Fifth|publisher=American Psychiatric Publishing|location=Arlington, VA|page=[https://archive.org/details/diagnosticstatis0005unse/page/189 189]|isbn=978-0-89042-555-8|url=https://archive.org/details/diagnosticstatis0005unse/page/189}}</ref>

== 焦慮與恐懼 ==
焦慮與恐懼不同。[[恐懼|恐懼]]是對當下威脅的相應[[認知|認知]]和[[情緒|情緒]]反應。<ref>[[Andreas_Dorschel|Andreas Dorschel]], ''Furcht und Angst.'' In: Dietmar Goltschnigg (ed.), ''Angst. Lähmender Stillstand und Motor des Fortschritts.'' Stauffenburg, Tübingen 2012, pp. 49–54</ref> 焦慮與[[戰鬥或逃跑反應|戰鬥或逃跑反應]]、防禦行為或逃避的具體行為有關。<ref>{{cite journal|title=On the distinction between fear and anxiety in a (post)pandemic world: a commentary on Schimmenti et al. (2020)|url=https://www.clinicalneuropsychiatry.org/download/on-the-distinction-between-fear-and-anxiety-in-a-postpandemic-world-a-commentary-on-schimmenti-et-al-2020/|journal=Clinical Neuropsychiatry|issue=3|doi=10.36131/cnfioritieditore20200307|year=2020|volume=17|pages=189–191|vauthors=Heeren A|access-date=2021-12-16|archive-date=2021-12-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211216235415/https://www.clinicalneuropsychiatry.org/download/on-the-distinction-between-fear-and-anxiety-in-a-postpandemic-world-a-commentary-on-schimmenti-et-al-2020/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 有一種錯誤的假設經常流傳，即焦慮只發生在被認為無法控制或不可避免的情況下，但並非總是如此。<ref>{{cite book|title=Handbook of emotions|vauthors=Öhman A|publisher=The Guilford Press|year=2000|isbn=978-1-57230-529-8|veditors=Lewis M, Haviland-Jones JM|location=New York|pages=[https://archive.org/details/handbookofemotio0000unse/page/573 573–93]|chapter=Fear and anxiety: Evolutionary, cognitive, and clinical perspectives|chapter-url=https://archive.org/details/handbookofemotio0000unse/page/573}}</ref> 大衛·巴洛 (David Barlow) 將焦慮定義為“一種面向未來的情緒狀態，在這種狀態下，人們還沒有準備好應對即將到來的負面事件”<ref>{{cite journal|title=Unraveling the mysteries of anxiety and its disorders from the perspective of emotion theory|date=November 2000|journal=The American Psychologist|issue=11|doi=10.1037/0003-066X.55.11.1247|volume=55|pages=1247–1263|pmid=11280938|vauthors=Barlow DH}}</ref>；因此，是對於當下或未來危機，將焦慮和恐懼區分開來。其他對焦慮的描述包括苦惱、極度擔心或憂慮。<ref>{{cite journal|title=What is the difference between existential anxiety and so called neurotic anxiety? 'The sine qua non of true vitality' an examination of the difference between existential anxiety and neurotic anxiety|journal=Existential Analysis|issue=2|year=2011|volume=22|id={{Gale|A288874227}}|vauthors=Iacovou S}}</ref> 在[[正面心理學|積極心理學]]中，焦慮被描述為由於[[因應_(心理學)|應對]]能力不足的困難挑戰而產生的心理狀態。<ref name="Finding Flow">{{cite book|title=Finding Flow|url=https://archive.org/details/findingflowpsych00csik|url-access=registration|vauthors=Csíkszentmihályi M|year=1997|isbn=9780465045136|name-list-style=vanc|author-link=Mihaly Csikszentmihalyi}}{{Page needed|date=May 2013}}</ref>

恐懼和焦慮可以分為四個領域：情緒體驗的持續時間、時間焦點、威脅的特異性，以及動機方向。恐懼是短暫的，關注當下，針對特定威脅，並有助於逃避威脅。焦慮是長效的，著眼於未來，廣泛關注瀰漫性威脅，並在接近潛在威脅時促進過度謹慎，並干擾建設性應對。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Differences between trait fear and trait anxiety: implications for psychopathology|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_clinical-psychology-review_2011-02_31_1/page/122|date=February 2011|journal=Clinical Psychology Review|issue=1|doi=10.1016/j.cpr.2010.08.004|volume=31|pages=122–137|pmid=20817337|vauthors=Sylvers P, Lilienfeld SO, LaPrairie JL}}</ref>

== 症狀 ==
焦慮可能表現為長期、持續的日常症狀，降低生活品質，稱為慢性（或廣泛性）焦慮，也可能表現為零星的、壓力性的[[恐慌發作|恐慌發作]]，稱為急性焦慮。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Generalized anxiety disorder: acute and chronic treatment|date=October 2004|journal=CNS Spectrums|issue=10|doi=10.1017/S1092852900022367|volume=9|pages=716–723|pmid=15448583|vauthors=Rynn MA, Brawman-Mintzer O|s2cid=24207457}}</ref> 焦慮症狀的數量、強度和頻率因人而異。雖然幾乎每個人在他們生命中的某個階段都經歷過焦慮，但大多數人並不會長期出現焦慮問題。

焦慮可能會導致精神和生理症狀。<ref name="WHO2009">{{cite book|author=World Health Organization|date=2009|title=Pharmacological Treatment of Mental Disorders in Primary Health Care|url=http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/44095/1/9789241547697_eng.pdf|location=Geneva|isbn=978-92-4-154769-7|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161120132530/http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/44095/1/9789241547697_eng.pdf|archive-date=2016-11-20}}</ref><ref name="TestaGiannuzzi2013partI">{{cite journal|title=Psychiatric emergencies (part I): psychiatric disorders causing organic symptoms|url=http://www.europeanreview.org/article/3083|date=February 2013|journal=European Review for Medical and Pharmacological Sciences|issue=Suppl 1|volume=17|pages=55–64|pmid=23436668|vauthors=Testa A, Giannuzzi R, Sollazzo F, Petrongolo L, Bernardini L, Daini S|access-date=2021-12-16|archive-date=2021-02-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210226131355/https://www.europeanreview.org/article/3083|dead-url=no}}{{open access}}</ref> 焦慮導致[[抑鬱|抑鬱]]的風險，甚至可能導致個人傷害自己。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.psychguides.com/guides/depression-hotline/|title=Depression Hotline {{!}} Call Our Free, 24 Hour Depression Helpline|work=PsychGuides.com|access-date=2018-10-11|archive-date=2018-10-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181011214543/https://www.psychguides.com/guides/depression-hotline/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

焦慮的行為影響，可能包括從過去引起焦慮或負面情緒的情況中退縮。<ref name="Barker, P. 2003" /> 其他影響可能包括[[睡眠|睡眠]]模式的改變、（日常）習慣的改變、食物攝入量的改變，以及運動神經緊張度的增加（如以足部敲擊等行為呈現）。<ref name="Barker, P. 2003" />

焦慮的情緒影響可能包括“憂慮或恐懼的感覺、注意力不集中、感覺緊張或神經質、預測最壞的情況、易怒、煩躁、觀察（和等待）危險的跡象（和發生），以及思緒一片空白”<ref>{{cite web|title=Anxiety attacks and disorders: Guide to the signs, symptoms, and treatment options.|url=http://www.helpguide.org/mental/anxiety_types_symptoms_treatment.htm|access-date=2009-03-03|date=June 2008|work=Helpguide|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090307161028/http://www.helpguide.org/mental/anxiety_types_symptoms_treatment.htm|archive-date=2009-03-07|vauthors=Smith M|url-status=dead}}</ref>，還有“帶有負面情緒的夢境、對感覺的痴迷、[[似曾相識|似曾相識]]的感覺、受困在自己心智中的感覺、對一切事物感到害怕”<ref>{{cite web|title=Anxiety Symptoms, Causes, Treatment|url=http://www.anxietycentre.com/anxiety-symptoms.shtml|access-date=2009-03-03|date=2021-10-13|work=Anxiety Centre|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090307132218/http://www.anxietycentre.com/anxiety-symptoms.shtml|archive-date=2009-03-07|vauthors=Folk J|veditors=Liashko V|orig-date=1987|url-status=live}}</ref>等。也可能包含一種模糊不清的無助感體驗與感受。<ref>{{cite journal|title=The Effectiveness of Multidimensional Counseling in the Intervention of Student Anxiety.|date=September 2020|journal=Addictive Disorders & Their Treatment|issue=3|doi=10.1097/ADT.0000000000000187|volume=19|pages=131–5|vauthors=Milfayetty S, Fadli RP, Ifdil I, Zola N, Amalianita B, Putri YE, Ardi Z|s2cid=209255441}}</ref>

焦慮的生理症狀可能包括：<ref name="WHO20092">{{cite book|author=World Health Organization|date=2009|title=Pharmacological Treatment of Mental Disorders in Primary Health Care|url=http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/44095/1/9789241547697_eng.pdf|location=Geneva|isbn=978-92-4-154769-7|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161120132530/http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/44095/1/9789241547697_eng.pdf|archive-date=2016-11-20}}</ref><ref name="TestaGiannuzzi2013partI2">{{cite journal|title=Psychiatric emergencies (part I): psychiatric disorders causing organic symptoms|url=http://www.europeanreview.org/article/3083|date=February 2013|journal=European Review for Medical and Pharmacological Sciences|issue=Suppl 1|volume=17|pages=55–64|pmid=23436668|vauthors=Testa A, Giannuzzi R, Sollazzo F, Petrongolo L, Bernardini L, Daini S|access-date=2021-12-16|archive-date=2021-02-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210226131355/https://www.europeanreview.org/article/3083|dead-url=no}}{{open access}}</ref>

* 神經系統：如頭痛、感覺異常（英語：paresthesias）、肌束震顫（英語：fasciculations）、眩暈或[[頭重腳輕|頭重腳輕]]等。
* 消化系統：如腹痛、噁心、腹瀉、消化不良、口乾等。在焦慮狀態下釋放的壓力荷爾蒙會影響腸道功能，並可能表現出可能導致或加劇[[大腸激躁症|大腸激躁症]]的身體症狀。
* 呼吸系統：如呼吸急促或嘆息。
* 心臟：如[[心悸|心悸]]、[[心跳過速|心跳過速]]或胸痛。
* 肌肉：如疲勞、顫抖或手足抽搐。
* 皮膚：發汗或發癢。
* 泌尿生殖系統：如[[頻尿症|頻尿]]、尿急、[[性交疼痛|性交困難]]或陽痿、[[慢性前列腺炎/慢性骨盆疼痛綜合症|慢性前列腺炎/慢性骨盆疼痛綜合症]]等。

== 焦慮症之合併症 ==
[[焦慮症|焦慮症]]經常與其他精神健康障礙一起發生，特別是[[重度抑鬱症|重度抑鬱症]]、[[躁鬱症|雙相情感障礙]]、[[進食障礙|飲食障礙]]或某些[[人格障礙|人格障礙]]。 它也經常出現在人格特徵中，例如[[神經質|神經質]]。 這種觀察到的共現部分是由於這些特徵和焦慮之間共享的[[遺傳|遺傳]]和環境影響。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Correction to: Psychiatric genetics and the structure of psychopathology|date=March 2019|journal=Molecular Psychiatry|issue=3|doi=10.1038/s41380-018-0026-4|volume=24|pages=471|pmid=29540840|vauthors=Smoller JW, Andreassen OA, Edenberg HJ, Faraone SV, Glatt SJ, Kendler KS|doi-access=free}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Major Depression and Generalised Anxiety Disorder|date=July 2004|journal=FOCUS|issue=3|doi=10.1176/foc.2.3.416|volume=2|pages=416–425|vauthors=Kendler KS}}</ref>

== 風險因素 ==
焦慮症部分來自遺傳。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Robert Plomin, John C. DeFries, Valerie S. Knopik, Jenae M. Neiderhiser, Behavioral Genetics (6th Edition)|date=2013-06-16|journal=Behavior Genetics|issue=4|doi=10.1007/s10519-013-9598-6|volume=43|pages=360–361|vauthors=Reynolds CA|s2cid=141211176}}</ref> 環境因素也很重要。對於[[雙胞胎|雙胞胎]]的研究表明，個體所處特定環境對焦慮有很大的影響，而共享的環境影響（以相同方式影響雙胞胎的環境）在童年時期起作用，但在青春期下降。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Genetics of anxiety disorders: the complex road from DSM to DNA|date=November 2009|journal=Depression and Anxiety|issue=11|doi=10.1002/da.20623|volume=26|pages=965–975|pmid=19885930|vauthors=Smoller JW, Block SR, Young MM|s2cid=35349081}}</ref> 與焦慮相關的特定測量“環境”包括[[虐待兒童|童年受虐]]、家族精神疾病史和貧困。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Anxiety disorders|date=May 2017|journal=Nature Reviews. Disease Primers|issue=1|doi=10.1038/nrdp.2017.24|volume=3|pages=17024|pmid=28470168|vauthors=Craske MG, Stein MB, Eley TC, Milad MR, Holmes A, Rapee RM, Wittchen HU|s2cid=52852105}}</ref> 焦慮也與藥物使用有關，包括酒精、咖啡因和[[苯二氮卓類|苯二氮卓類]]藥物（通常用於治療焦慮症）。

=== 疾病情況 ===
許多疾病會引起焦慮。這包括影響呼吸能力的疾病，如[[慢性阻塞性肺病|慢性阻塞性肺病]]和[[哮喘|哮喘]]，以及在臨近死亡時經常發生的呼吸困難。引起腹痛或胸痛的疾病會引起焦慮，在某些情況下可能是焦慮的軀體化；一些性功能障礙也是如此。影響面部或皮膚的疾病會導致[[社交焦慮|社交焦慮]]，尤其是在青少年中，而[[發育障礙|發育障礙]]通常也會導致兒童的社交焦慮。癌症等危及生命的疾病也會引起焦慮。

此外，某些[[疾病|器質性疾病]]可能會出現焦慮或類似焦慮的症狀。<ref name="WHO20092" /><ref name="TestaGiannuzzi2013partIII">{{cite journal|title=Psychiatric emergencies (part III): psychiatric symptoms resulting from organic diseases|url=http://www.europeanreview.org/article/3087|date=February 2013|journal=European Review for Medical and Pharmacological Sciences|issue=Suppl 1|volume=17|pages=86–99|pmid=23436670|vauthors=Testa A, Giannuzzi R, Daini S, Bernardini L, Petrongolo L, Gentiloni Silveri N|access-date=2021-12-16|archive-date=2021-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210304154235/https://www.europeanreview.org/article/3087|dead-url=no}}{{open access}}</ref> 這些疾病包括某些內分泌疾病（[[甲狀腺功能減退症|甲狀腺功能減退症]]和[[甲狀腺功能亢進症|甲狀腺功能亢進症]]、高催乳素血症（英語：Hyperprolactinaemia））<ref name="TestaGiannuzzi2013partIII">{{cite journal|title=Psychiatric emergencies (part III): psychiatric symptoms resulting from organic diseases|url=http://www.europeanreview.org/article/3087|date=February 2013|journal=European Review for Medical and Pharmacological Sciences|issue=Suppl 1|volume=17|pages=86–99|pmid=23436670|vauthors=Testa A, Giannuzzi R, Daini S, Bernardini L, Petrongolo L, Gentiloni Silveri N}}{{open access}}</ref><ref name="Samuels2008">{{cite journal|title=Cognitive function in untreated hypothyroidism and hyperthyroidism|date=October 2008|journal=Current Opinion in Endocrinology, Diabetes and Obesity|issue=5|doi=10.1097/MED.0b013e32830eb84c|volume=15|pages=429–433|pmid=18769215|vauthors=Samuels MH|s2cid=27235034}}</ref>、代謝失調（[[糖尿病|糖尿病]]）<ref name="TestaGiannuzzi2013partIII">{{cite journal|title=Psychiatric emergencies (part III): psychiatric symptoms resulting from organic diseases|url=http://www.europeanreview.org/article/3087|date=February 2013|journal=European Review for Medical and Pharmacological Sciences|issue=Suppl 1|volume=17|pages=86–99|pmid=23436670|vauthors=Testa A, Giannuzzi R, Daini S, Bernardini L, Petrongolo L, Gentiloni Silveri N}}{{open access}}</ref><ref name="BuchbergerHuppertz2016">{{cite journal|title=Symptoms of depression and anxiety in youth with type 1 diabetes: A systematic review and meta-analysis|date=August 2016|journal=Psychoneuroendocrinology|doi=10.1016/j.psyneuen.2016.04.019|volume=70|pages=70–84|pmid=27179232|vauthors=Buchberger B, Huppertz H, Krabbe L, Lux B, Mattivi JT, Siafarikas A|s2cid=19858996}}</ref><ref name="GrigsbyAnderson2002">{{cite journal|title=Prevalence of anxiety in adults with diabetes: a systematic review|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-psychosomatic-research_2002-12_53_6/page/1053|date=December 2002|journal=Journal of Psychosomatic Research|issue=6|doi=10.1016/S0022-3999(02)00417-8|volume=53|pages=1053–1060|pmid=12479986|vauthors=Grigsby AB, Anderson RJ, Freedland KE, Clouse RE, Lustman PJ}}</ref>、維生素不足狀態（[[維生素D|維生素D]]、[[核黄素|B2]]、[[維生素B12|B12]]、[[葉酸|葉酸]]等低於身體正常運作所需水平）<ref name="TestaGiannuzzi2013partIII">{{cite journal|title=Psychiatric emergencies (part III): psychiatric symptoms resulting from organic diseases|url=http://www.europeanreview.org/article/3087|date=February 2013|journal=European Review for Medical and Pharmacological Sciences|issue=Suppl 1|volume=17|pages=86–99|pmid=23436670|vauthors=Testa A, Giannuzzi R, Daini S, Bernardini L, Petrongolo L, Gentiloni Silveri N}}{{open access}}</ref>、胃腸道疾病（[[乳糜瀉|乳糜瀉]]、非腹腔麩質敏感性（英語：Non-celiac gluten sensitivity，縮寫作NCGS，或稱gluten sensitivity）、[[炎症性腸病|炎症性腸病]]）<ref name="ZingoneSwift2015">{{cite journal|title=Psychological morbidity of celiac disease: A review of the literature|date=April 2015|journal=United European Gastroenterology Journal|issue=2|doi=10.1177/2050640614560786|volume=3|pages=136–145|pmc=4406898|pmid=25922673|vauthors=Zingone F, Swift GL, Card TR, Sanders DS, Ludvigsson JF, Bai JC}}</ref><ref name="MolinaInfanteSantolaria2015SystematicReview">{{cite journal|title=Systematic review: noncoeliac gluten sensitivity|date=May 2015|journal=Alimentary Pharmacology & Therapeutics|issue=9|doi=10.1111/apt.13155|volume=41|pages=807–820|pmid=25753138|vauthors=Molina-Infante J, Santolaria S, Sanders DS, Fernández-Bañares F|s2cid=207050854}}</ref><ref name="NeuendorfHarding2016">{{cite journal|title=Depression and anxiety in patients with Inflammatory Bowel Disease: A systematic review|date=August 2016|journal=Journal of Psychosomatic Research|doi=10.1016/j.jpsychores.2016.06.001|volume=87|pages=70–80|pmid=27411754|vauthors=Neuendorf R, Harding A, Stello N, Hanes D, Wahbeh H}}</ref>、[[心臟病|心臟病]]、血液病（[[貧血|貧血]]）<ref name="TestaGiannuzzi2013partIII">{{cite journal|title=Psychiatric emergencies (part III): psychiatric symptoms resulting from organic diseases|url=http://www.europeanreview.org/article/3087|date=February 2013|journal=European Review for Medical and Pharmacological Sciences|issue=Suppl 1|volume=17|pages=86–99|pmid=23436670|vauthors=Testa A, Giannuzzi R, Daini S, Bernardini L, Petrongolo L, Gentiloni Silveri N}}{{open access}}</ref>、腦血管意外（[[短暫性腦缺血發作|短暫性腦缺血發作]]、[[中風|中風]]）<ref name="TestaGiannuzzi2013partIII">{{cite journal|title=Psychiatric emergencies (part III): psychiatric symptoms resulting from organic diseases|url=http://www.europeanreview.org/article/3087|date=February 2013|journal=European Review for Medical and Pharmacological Sciences|issue=Suppl 1|volume=17|pages=86–99|pmid=23436670|vauthors=Testa A, Giannuzzi R, Daini S, Bernardini L, Petrongolo L, Gentiloni Silveri N}}{{open access}}</ref>和腦退化性疾病（[[帕金森病|帕金森病]]、[[失智症|癡呆]]、[[多發性硬化症|多發性硬化症]]、[[亨廷頓病|亨廷頓病]]）等。<ref name="TestaGiannuzzi2013partIII">{{cite journal|title=Psychiatric emergencies (part III): psychiatric symptoms resulting from organic diseases|url=http://www.europeanreview.org/article/3087|date=February 2013|journal=European Review for Medical and Pharmacological Sciences|issue=Suppl 1|volume=17|pages=86–99|pmid=23436670|vauthors=Testa A, Giannuzzi R, Daini S, Bernardini L, Petrongolo L, Gentiloni Silveri N}}{{open access}}</ref><ref name="ZhaoTan2016">{{cite journal|title=The prevalence of neuropsychiatric symptoms in Alzheimer's disease: Systematic review and meta-analysis|date=January 2016|journal=Journal of Affective Disorders|doi=10.1016/j.jad.2015.09.069|volume=190|pages=264–271|pmid=26540080|display-authors=6|vauthors=Zhao QF, Tan L, Wang HF, Jiang T, Tan MS, Tan L, Xu W, Li JQ, Wang J, Lai TJ, Yu JT}}</ref><ref name="WenChan2016">{{cite journal|title=Depression, anxiety, and apathy in Parkinson's disease: insights from neuroimaging studies|date=June 2016|journal=European Journal of Neurology|issue=6|doi=10.1111/ene.13002|volume=23|pages=1001–1019|pmc=5084819|pmid=27141858|vauthors=Wen MC, Chan LL, Tan LC, Tan EK}}</ref><ref name="MarrieReingold2015">{{cite journal|title=The incidence and prevalence of psychiatric disorders in multiple sclerosis: a systematic review|date=March 2015|journal=Multiple Sclerosis|issue=3|doi=10.1177/1352458514564487|volume=21|pages=305–317|pmc=4429164|pmid=25583845|display-authors=6|vauthors=Marrie RA, Reingold S, Cohen J, Stuve O, Trojano M, Sorensen PS, Cutter G, Reider N}}</ref>

=== 物質誘發 ===
具有高[[四氫大麻酚|四氫大麻酚]]含量的大麻會引起或加劇焦慮，但是大麻中另一種化合物[[大麻二酚|大麻二酚]]在許多研究中已被證明可以減輕焦慮症狀。<ref>{{Cite web|title=CBD for anxiety - can it help?|url=https://www.leafie.co.uk/articles/cbd-anxiety/|access-date=2021-10-28|website=leafie|language=en-GB|archive-date=2022-01-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220104120025/https://www.leafie.co.uk/articles/cbd-anxiety/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

雖然許多人經常報告用該些物質（酒精、煙草、鎮靜劑（包括處方[[苯二氮卓類|苯二氮卓類]]藥物）、[[阿片類藥物|阿片類藥物]]（包括處方止痛藥和[[海洛因|海洛因]]等非法藥物）、興奮劑（例如咖啡因、[[古柯鹼|古柯鹼]]和[[安非他明|安非他明]]）、[[致幻劑|致幻劑]]、[[大麻|大麻]]等）自我治療焦慮，但藥物焦慮的改善通常是短暫的（長期焦慮會惡化，有時一旦藥物作用消失就會出現急性焦慮）並往往被誇大。<ref>{{Cite web|title=CDC – The Emergency Response Safety and Health Database: Systemic Agent: BENZENE – NIOSH|url=https://www.cdc.gov/niosh/ershdb/emergencyresponsecard_29750032.html|access-date=2016-01-27|website=www.cdc.gov|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160117001341/http://www.cdc.gov/niosh/ershdb/emergencyresponsecard_29750032.html|archive-date=2016-01-17|url-status=live}}</ref>

=== 心理方面 ===
某些[[因應_(心理學)|應對]]行為模式（如僵化的問題解決方式、否認、迴避、衝動、極端的自我期望、消極思想、情感不穩定和無法專注於問題）與焦慮有關。焦慮也與自己悲觀的結果預期，及其如何應對負面反饋有關並持續存在。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Anxiety and feedback negativity|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_psychophysiology_2010-09_47_5/page/961|date=September 2010|journal=Psychophysiology|issue=5|doi=10.1111/j.1469-8986.2010.00997.x|volume=47|pages=961–967|pmid=20374540|vauthors=Gu R, Huang YX, Luo YJ}}{{primary source inline|date=May 2013}}</ref> 已發現氣質（如[[神經質|神經質]]）<ref name="NeuroticismMA">{{cite journal|title=Neuroticism's prospective association with mental disorders halves after adjustment for baseline symptoms and psychiatric history, but the adjusted association hardly decays with time: a meta-analysis on 59 longitudinal/prospective studies with 443 313 participants|url=https://zenodo.org/record/895885|date=October 2016|journal=Psychological Medicine|issue=14|doi=10.1017/S0033291716001653|volume=46|pages=2883–2906|pmid=27523506|vauthors=Jeronimus BF, Kotov R, Riese H, Ormel J|s2cid=23548727|access-date=2021-12-16|archive-date=2019-12-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191229175420/https://zenodo.org/record/895885|dead-url=no}}</ref>和態度（如[[悲觀主義|悲觀主義]]）是焦慮的潛在因素。<ref name="Bienvenu Ginsburg 2007">{{cite journal|title=Prevention of anxiety disorders|date=December 2007|journal=International Review of Psychiatry|issue=6|doi=10.1080/09540260701797837|volume=19|pages=647–654|pmid=18092242|vauthors=Bienvenu OJ, Ginsburg GS|s2cid=95140}}</ref>

[[認知扭曲|認知扭曲]]，如過度概括、災難化、[[讀心術|讀心術]]、[[情緒化推理|情緒化推理]]和心理過濾（英語：mental filter）等，都會導致焦慮。例如，認為不好的事情“總是”發生的過於籠統的信念，可能會導致某人對即使是最低風險的情況也有過度的恐懼，並由於尷尬的預期焦慮而避免良性社交場合。此外，高度焦慮的人也可以創造未來的壓力生活事件。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Negative life events and symptoms of depression and anxiety: stress causation and/or stress generation|journal=Anxiety, Stress, and Coping|issue=4|doi=10.1080/10615806.2015.1005078|year=2015|volume=28|pages=357–371|pmc=4772121|pmid=25572915|vauthors=Phillips AC, Carroll D, Der G}}</ref> 總之，這些發現表明，焦慮的想法會導致預期的焦慮以及壓力事件，從而導致更多的焦慮。這種不健康的想法可以成為成功治療[[認知療法|認知療法]]的目標。

[[心理動力學|心理動力學]]理論認為，焦慮通常是對抗[[無意識|無意識]]願望或恐懼的結果，這些願望或恐懼透過適應不良的[[心理防衛機制|防禦機制]]（如抑制（英語：suppression）、壓抑（英語：repression）、預期、回歸（英語：regression）、軀體化（英語：somatization）、被動攻擊（英語：passive aggression）、分離（英語：dissociation））表現出來，這些機制發展以適應早期[[客體關係理論|對象]]的問題（如照顧者）和童年時期的[[移情|移情]]失敗。例如，父母對憤怒的持續勸阻，可能會導致對憤怒情緒的壓抑/抑制，當被他人激怒時，這種情緒表現為胃腸道不適（軀體化），而憤怒仍然是無意識的並且在個人的意識之外。這種衝突可以成為心理動力學療法成功治療的目標。雖然心理動力學療法傾向於探索焦慮的潛在根源，但[[認知行為療法|認知行為療法]]也已被證明是一種透過改變非理性想法和不良行為來成功治療焦慮的方法。

==== 演化心理學 ====
[[演化心理學|演化心理學]]的一種解釋是，增加的焦慮有助於提高對環境中潛在威脅的警惕性（英語：vigilance，心理學術語），並增加對此類可能威脅採取主動行動的傾向。 這可能會導致誤報，但患有焦慮症的人也可能會避免真正的威脅。 這或許可以解釋為什麼焦慮的人不太可能因事故而死亡。<ref>{{cite journal|title=The bright side of being blue: depression as an adaptation for analyzing complex problems|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_psychological-review_2009-07_116_3/page/620|date=July 2009|journal=Psychological Review|issue=3|doi=10.1037/a0016242|volume=116|pages=620–654|pmc=2734449|pmid=19618990|vauthors=Andrews PW, Thomson JA}}</ref> 有充分的經驗證據表明焦慮具有適應性價值。 在魚群裡，膽小的魚比大膽的魚更有可能在捕食者面前存活下來。<ref>{{Cite book|vauthors=Gluckman P|title=Principles of Evolutionary Medicine|url=https://archive.org/details/principlesofevol0000gluc|publisher=Oxford University Press|year=2009|isbn=978-0199236398|pages=[https://archive.org/details/principlesofevol0000gluc/page/249 249]}}</ref>

當人們面臨令人不快和潛在有害的刺激時，例如難聞的氣味或味道，[[正子斷層造影|正子斷層造影]]顯示[[杏仁核|杏仁核]]中的血流量增加。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Emotion, olfaction, and the human amygdala: amygdala activation during aversive olfactory stimulation|date=April 1997|journal=Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America|issue=8|doi=10.1073/pnas.94.8.4119|volume=94|pages=4119–4124|bibcode=1997PNAS...94.4119Z|pmc=20578|pmid=9108115|vauthors=Zald DH, Pardo JV|doi-access=free}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Neural correlates of tasting concentrated quinine and sugar solutions|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-neurophysiology_2002-02_87_2/page/1068|date=February 2002|journal=Journal of Neurophysiology|issue=2|doi=10.1152/jn.00358.2001|volume=87|pages=1068–1075|pmid=11826070|vauthors=Zald DH, Hagen MC, Pardo JV|s2cid=6278342}}</ref> 在這些研究中，參與者還報告了中度焦慮。 這可能表明焦慮是一種保護機制，旨在防止有機體從事潛在的有害行為。

=== 社會方面 ===
焦慮的社會風險因素包括創傷史（例如，身體、性或情感虐待或攻擊）、[[霸凌|欺凌]]、早期生活經歷和育兒因素（例如，（遭）拒絕、缺乏（心理）溫暖、高度敵意、嚴厲的紀律、父母的高度負面影響、誘導焦慮的育兒模式、（家庭）功能失調和吸毒行為的建模、情緒沮喪、社會化不理想、負面的[[依附理論|依附]]模式、虐待和童年時期遭（家長）忽視）、文化因素（例如，堅忍的家庭/文化、受迫害的少數民族，包括身心障礙者及[[性少數者|性少數者]]等）和[[社會經濟地位|社會經濟地位]]（例如，教育程度偏低、失業、貧困等）。<ref>{{cite book|chapter-url=http://books.nap.edu/openbook.php?record_id=12480&page=530|chapter=Table E-4 Risk Factors for Anxiety|page=530|veditors=O'Connell ME, Boat T, Warner KE|publisher=National Academies Press|title=Prevention of Mental Disorders, Substance Abuse, and Problem Behaviors: A Developmental Perspective|year=2009|isbn=978-0-309-12674-8|doi=10.17226/12480|pmid=20662125|vauthors=((National Research Council (Us) Institute Of Medicine (Us) Committee On The Prevention Of Mental Disorders Substance Abuse Among Children, Youth, and Young Adults))|s2cid=142581788|access-date=2021-12-16|archive-date=2014-04-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140418234307/http://books.nap.edu/openbook.php?record_id=12480&page=530|dead-url=no}}</ref> 2019 年對 50 多項研究的綜合系統審查表明，在美國，糧食不安全與抑鬱、焦慮和睡眠障礙密切相關。<ref>{{cite journal|title=A Systematic Review and Meta-analysis of Depression, Anxiety, and Sleep Disorders in US Adults with Food Insecurity|date=December 2019|journal=Journal of General Internal Medicine|issue=12|doi=10.1007/s11606-019-05202-4|volume=34|pages=2874–2882|pmc=6854208|pmid=31385212|vauthors=Arenas DJ, Thomas A, Wang J, DeLisser HM}}</ref> 與糧食安全的個體相比，糧食不安全的個體焦慮測試呈陽性的風險增加了近 3 倍。

==应对==
应对焦虑的主要策略包括：<ref>{{cite book|title=心理学|year=2002|isbn=7-310-01692-0|author=张厚粲|page=275-277}}</ref>
#认清焦虑状况
#克服焦虑的三个原则：不回避；正面迎战；做记录
#学会放松自己
#运用[[想象|想象]]减轻焦虑
#进行[[理性|理性]]思考
#接受专业治疗

== 治療 ==
管理有焦慮症狀的人的第一步是評估潛在的醫療原因的可能存在，識別這些原因對於決定正確的治療至關重要。<ref name="WHO20092" /><ref name="TestaGiannuzzi2013partIII" /> 焦慮症狀可能會掩蓋[[疾病|器質性疾病]]，或與軀體疾病相關或由軀體疾病引起。<ref name="WHO20092" /><ref name="TestaGiannuzzi2013partIII" /><ref name="TestaGiannuzzi2013partII">{{cite journal|title=Psychiatric emergencies (part II): psychiatric disorders coexisting with organic diseases|url=http://www.europeanreview.org/article/3085|date=February 2013|journal=European Review for Medical and Pharmacological Sciences|issue=Suppl 1|volume=17|pages=65–85|pmid=23436669|vauthors=Testa A, Giannuzzi R, Sollazzo F, Petrongolo L, Bernardini L, Dain S|access-date=2021-12-16|archive-date=2021-05-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210505213014/https://www.europeanreview.org/article/3085|dead-url=no}}{{open access}}</ref><ref name="TestaGiannuzzi2013partI2" />

[[認知行為療法|認知行為療法]] (CBT) 對焦慮症有效，是一線治療方法。<ref name="NEJM2015">{{cite journal|title=CLINICAL PRACTICE. Generalized Anxiety Disorder|date=November 2015|journal=The New England Journal of Medicine|issue=21|doi=10.1056/nejmcp1502514|volume=373|pages=2059–2068|pmid=26580998|vauthors=Stein MB, Sareen J}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Psychological treatment of generalized anxiety disorder: a meta-analysis|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_clinical-psychology-review_2014-03_34_2/page/130|date=March 2014|journal=Clinical Psychology Review|issue=2|doi=10.1016/j.cpr.2014.01.002|volume=34|pages=130–140|pmid=24487344|vauthors=Cuijpers P, Sijbrandij M, Koole S, Huibers M, Berking M, Andersson G}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Cognitive behavioral therapy in anxiety disorders: current state of the evidence|journal=Dialogues in Clinical Neuroscience|issue=4|doi=10.31887/DCNS.2011.13.4/cotte|year=2011|volume=13|pages=413–421|pmc=3263389|pmid=22275847|vauthors=Otte C}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Psychological therapies for panic disorder with or without agoraphobia in adults: a network meta-analysis|date=April 2016|journal=The Cochrane Database of Systematic Reviews|doi=10.1002/14651858.CD011004.pub2|volume=4|pages=CD011004|pmc=7104662|pmid=27071857|vauthors=Pompoli A, Furukawa TA, Imai H, Tajika A, Efthimiou O, Salanti G}}</ref><ref name="Ol2016">{{cite journal|title=Therapist-supported Internet cognitive behavioural therapy for anxiety disorders in adults|date=March 2016|journal=The Cochrane Database of Systematic Reviews|issue=3|doi=10.1002/14651858.cd011565.pub2|volume=2016|pages=CD011565|pmc=7077612|pmid=26968204|vauthors=Olthuis JV, Watt MC, Bailey K, Hayden JA, Stewart SH}}</ref> 當透過[[互聯網|互聯網]]進行時，CBT似乎同樣有效。<ref name="Ol2016">{{cite journal|title=Therapist-supported Internet cognitive behavioural therapy for anxiety disorders in adults|date=March 2016|journal=The Cochrane Database of Systematic Reviews|issue=3|doi=10.1002/14651858.cd011565.pub2|volume=2016|pages=CD011565|pmc=7077612|pmid=26968204|vauthors=Olthuis JV, Watt MC, Bailey K, Hayden JA, Stewart SH}}</ref> 雖然心理健康[[應用程式|應用程式]]的證據很有希望，但它是初步的。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Smartphones for smarter delivery of mental health programs: a systematic review|date=November 2013|journal=Journal of Medical Internet Research|issue=11|doi=10.2196/jmir.2791|volume=15|pages=e247|pmc=3841358|pmid=24240579|vauthors=Donker T, Petrie K, Proudfoot J, Clarke J, Birch MR, Christensen H}}</ref>

精神藥物治療可以與 CBT 並行使用，也可以單獨使用。 一般來說，大多數焦慮症對一線藥物反應良好。 此類藥物也用作抗抑鬱藥，是[[選擇性5-羥色胺再攝取抑製劑|選擇性5-羥色胺再攝取抑製劑]]和 [[5-羥色胺和去甲腎上腺素再攝取抑制劑|5-羥色胺-去甲腎上腺素再攝取抑製劑]]，它們透過阻斷特定神經遞質的再攝取並導致這些神經遞質的可用性增加而起作用。 此外，[[苯二氮卓類|苯二氮卓類]]藥物通常用於患有焦慮症的人。 苯二氮卓類藥物透過調節 GABA 和增加其受體結合產生抗焦慮反應。 第三種常見的治療方法涉及一類稱為[[血清素受體激動劑|血清素激動劑]]的藥物。 這類藥物的作用是透過增加血清素對 5-HT1A 受體的作用來啟動對 5-HT1A 受體的生理反應。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Introduction of Presentations, ICCSE2014|url=http://dx.doi.org/10.1109/iccse.2014.6926415|date=August 2014|journal=2014 9th International Conference on Computer Science & Education|publisher=IEEE|doi=10.1109/iccse.2014.6926415|pages=19|isbn=978-1-4799-2951-1}}</ref> 其他治療選擇包括[[普瑞巴林|普瑞巴林]]、[[三環類抗抑鬱藥|三環類抗抑鬱藥]]和[[嗎氯貝胺|嗎氯貝胺]]等。<ref name="Bandelow_2017">{{cite journal|title=Treatment of anxiety disorders|date=June 2017|journal=Dialogues in Clinical Neuroscience|issue=2|doi=10.31887/DCNS.2017.19.2/bbandelow|volume=19|pages=93–107|pmc=5573566|pmid=28867934|vauthors=Bandelow B, Michaelis S, Wedekind D}}</ref>

== 預防 ==
上述風險因素為預防提供了自然途徑。 2017 年的一項審查發現，心理或教育干預措施對於預防不同人群類型的焦慮症具有微小但具統計學意義的益處。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Effectiveness of Psychological and/or Educational Interventions in the Prevention of Anxiety: A Systematic Review, Meta-analysis, and Meta-regression|date=October 2017|journal=JAMA Psychiatry|issue=10|doi=10.1001/jamapsychiatry.2017.2509|volume=74|pages=1021–1029|pmc=5710546|pmid=28877316|display-authors=6|vauthors=Moreno-Peral P, Conejo-Cerón S, Rubio-Valera M, Fernández A, Navas-Campaña D, Rodríguez-Morejón A, Motrico E, Rigabert A, Luna JD, Martín-Pérez C, Rodríguez-Bayón A, Ballesta-Rodríguez MI, Luciano JV, Bellón JÁ}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Preventing anxiety with psychological and educational interventions|url=https://www.nationalelfservice.net/mental-health/anxiety/preventing-anxiety-with-psychological-and-educational-interventions/|date=2018-02-19|website=National Elf Service|vauthors=Pote I|access-date=2021-12-16|archive-date=2021-12-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211216143836/https://www.nationalelfservice.net/mental-health/anxiety/preventing-anxiety-with-psychological-and-educational-interventions/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|doi=10.1016/B978-0-12-813495-5.00008-5|chapter=Targeting anxiety sensitivity as a prevention strategy|title=The Clinician's Guide to Anxiety Sensitivity Treatment and Assessment|pages=145–178|year=2019|vauthors=Schmidt NB, Allan NP, Knapp AA, Capron D|isbn=978-0-12-813495-5|s2cid=81782119}}</ref>

